%N A183664 Number of (n+1) X 2 0..6 arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 12.
%H A183664 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A183664/b183664.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..200</a>
%H A183664 Christian Krause, <a href="/A183664/a183664.txt">Proof of formulas</a>, Jun 12 2026.
%H A183664 <a href="/index/Rec#order_07">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (28,-322,1960,-6769,13132,-13068,5040).
%F A183664 a(n) = 28*a(n-1) - 322*a(n-2) + 1960*a(n-3) - 6769*a(n-4) + 13132*a(n-5) - 13068*a(n-6) + 5040*a(n-7).
%F A183664 G.f.: x*(231 - 5243*x + 47033*x^2 - 211729*x^3 + 499000*x^4 - 574812*x^5 + 246960*x^6) / ((1 - x)*(1 - 2*x)*(1 - 3*x)*(1 - 4*x)*(1 - 5*x)*(1 - 6*x)*(1 - 7*x)). - _Colin Barker_, Apr 02 2018
%F A183664 a(n) = 7*7^n + 12*6^n + 10*5^n + 8*4^n + 6*3^n + 4*2^n + 2. - _Christian Krause_, Jun 12 2026
%e A183664 Some solutions for 3 X 2:
%e A183664 ..4..4....5..3....1..5....3..3....4..6....6..0....4..3....4..2....2..3....3..1
%e A183664 ..4..0....4..0....3..3....1..5....1..1....2..4....2..3....2..4....6..1....6..2
%e A183664 ..6..2....5..3....3..3....6..0....4..6....5..1....4..3....3..3....1..4....3..1
%t A183664 A183664[n_] := 2*Sum[k^(n+1), {k, 2, 6}] + 7^(n+1) + 2;
